verses.text_plain: And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days.
verses.verse_html: 1And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days.

verses.text_plain: Gather yourselves together, and hear, ye sons of Jacob; and hearken unto Israel your father.
verses.verse_html: 2Gather yourselves together, and hear, ye sons of Jacob; and hearken unto Israel your father.

verses.text_plain: Reuben, thou art my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my strength, the excellency of dignity, and the excellency of power:
verses.verse_html: 3Reuben, thou art my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my strength, the excellency of dignity, and the excellency of power:

verses.text_plain: Unstable as water, thou shalt not excel; because thou wentest up to thy father’s bed; then defiledst thou it: he went up to my couch.
verses.verse_html:
4Unstable as water, thou shalt not excel; because thou wentest up to thy father’s bed; then defiledst thou it: he went up to my couch. ▼
▼ thou shalt…: Heb. do not thou excel
 , ▼
▼ he went…: or, my couch is gone

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thou shalt…: Heb. do not thou excel
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thou shalt…: Heb. do not thou excel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ he went…: or, my couch is gone
footnotes.body_html: ▼ he went…: or, my couch is gone

verses.text_plain: Simeon and Levi are brethren; instruments of cruelty are in their habitations.
verses.verse_html:
5Simeon and Levi are brethren; instruments of cruelty are in their habitations. ▼
▼ instruments…: or, their swords are weapons of violence

footnotes.body_text: ▼ instruments…: or, their swords are weapons of violence
footnotes.body_html: ▼ instruments…: or, their swords are weapons of violence

verses.text_plain: O my soul, come not thou into their secret; unto their assembly, mine honour, be not thou united: for in their anger they slew a man, and in their selfwill they digged down a wall.
verses.verse_html:
6O my soul, come not thou into their secret; unto their assembly, mine honour, be not thou united: for in their anger they slew a man, and in their selfwill they digged down a wall. ▼
▼ digged…: or, houghed oxen

footnotes.body_html: ▼ digged…: or, houghed oxen

verses.text_plain: Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce; and their wrath, for it was cruel: I will divide them in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.
verses.verse_html: 7Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce; and their wrath, for it was cruel: I will divide them in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.

verses.text_plain: Judah, thou art he whom thy brethren shall praise: thy hand shall be in the neck of thine enemies; thy father’s children shall bow down before thee.
verses.verse_html: 8Judah, thou art he whom thy brethren shall praise: thy hand shall be in the neck of thine enemies; thy father’s children shall bow down before thee.

verses.text_plain: Judah is a lion’s whelp: from the prey, my son, thou art gone up: he stooped down, he couched as a lion, and as an old lion; who shall rouse him up?
verses.verse_html: 9Judah is a lion’s whelp: from the prey, my son, thou art gone up: he stooped down, he couched as a lion, and as an old lion; who shall rouse him up?

verses.text_plain: The sceptre shall not depart from Judah, nor a lawgiver from between his feet, until Shiloh come; and unto him shall the gathering of the people be.
verses.verse_html: 10The sceptre shall not depart from Judah, nor a lawgiver from between his feet, until Shiloh come; and unto him shall the gathering of the people be.

verses.text_plain: Binding his foal unto the vine, and his ass’s colt unto the choice vine; he washed his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes:
verses.verse_html: 11Binding his foal unto the vine, and his ass’s colt unto the choice vine; he washed his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes:

verses.text_plain: His eyes shall be red with wine, and his teeth white with milk.
verses.verse_html: 12His eyes shall be red with wine, and his teeth white with milk.

verses.text_plain: Zebulun shall dwell at the haven of the sea; and he shall be for an haven of ships; and his border shall be unto Zidon.
verses.verse_html: 13Zebulun shall dwell at the haven of the sea; and he shall be for an haven of ships; and his border shall be unto Zidon.

verses.text_plain: Issachar is a strong ass couching down between two burdens:
verses.verse_html: 14Issachar is a strong ass couching down between two burdens:

verses.text_plain: And he saw that rest was good, and the land that it was pleasant; and bowed his shoulder to bear, and became a servant unto tribute.
verses.verse_html: 15And he saw that rest was good, and the land that it was pleasant; and bowed his shoulder to bear, and became a servant unto tribute.

verses.text_plain: Dan shall judge his people, as one of the tribes of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 16Dan shall judge his people, as one of the tribes of Israel.

verses.text_plain: Dan shall be a serpent by the way, an adder in the path, that biteth the horse heels, so that his rider shall fall backward.
verses.verse_html:
17Dan shall be a serpent by the way, an adder in the path, that biteth the horse heels, so that his rider shall fall backward. ▼
▼ an adder: Heb. an arrow-snake

footnotes.body_html: ▼ an adder: Heb. an arrow-snake

verses.text_plain: I have waited for thy salvation, O Lord.
verses.verse_html: 18I have waited for thy salvation, O Lord.

verses.text_plain: Gad, a troop shall overcome him: but he shall overcome at the last.
verses.verse_html: 19Gad, a troop shall overcome him: but he shall overcome at the last.

verses.text_plain: Out of Asher his bread shall be fat, and he shall yield royal dainties.
verses.verse_html: 20Out of Asher his bread shall be fat, and he shall yield royal dainties.

verses.text_plain: Naphtali is a hind let loose: he giveth goodly words.
verses.verse_html: 21Naphtali is a hind let loose: he giveth goodly words.

verses.text_plain: Joseph is a fruitful bough, even a fruitful bough by a well; whose branches run over the wall:
verses.verse_html:
22Joseph is a fruitful bough, even a fruitful bough by a well; whose branches run over the wall: ▼
▼ branches: Heb. daughters

verses.text_plain: The archers have sorely grieved him, and shot at him, and hated him:
verses.verse_html: 23The archers have sorely grieved him, and shot at him, and hated him:

verses.text_plain: But his bow abode in strength, and the arms of his hands were made strong by the hands of the mighty God of Jacob; (from thence is the shepherd, the stone of Israel:)
verses.verse_html: 24But his bow abode in strength, and the arms of his hands were made strong by the hands of the mighty God of Jacob; (from thence is the shepherd, the stone of Israel:)

verses.text_plain: Even by the God of thy father, who shall help thee; and by the Almighty, who shall bless thee with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lieth under, blessings of the breasts, and of the womb:
verses.verse_html: 25Even by the God of thy father, who shall help thee; and by the Almighty, who shall bless thee with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lieth under, blessings of the breasts, and of the womb:

verses.text_plain: The blessings of thy father have prevailed above the blessings of my progenitors unto the utmost bound of the everlasting hills: they shall be on the head of Joseph, and on the crown of the head of him that was separate from his brethren.
verses.verse_html: 26The blessings of thy father have prevailed above the blessings of my progenitors unto the utmost bound of the everlasting hills: they shall be on the head of Joseph, and on the crown of the head of him that was separate from his brethren.

tokens.text: they shall be on the head
and on the crown of the head

verses.text_plain: Benjamin shall ravin as a wolf: in the morning he shall devour the prey, and at night he shall divide the spoil.
verses.verse_html: 27Benjamin shall ravin as a wolf: in the morning he shall devour the prey, and at night he shall divide the spoil.

verses.text_plain: All these are the twelve tribes of Israel: and this is it that their father spake unto them, and blessed them; every one according to his blessing he blessed them.
verses.verse_html: 28All these are the twelve tribes of Israel: and this is it that their father spake unto them, and blessed them; every one according to his blessing he blessed them.

verses.text_plain: And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered unto my people: bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,
verses.verse_html: 29And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered unto my people: bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,

tokens.text: unto them, I am to be gathered

verses.text_plain: In the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite for a possession of a buryingplace.
verses.verse_html: 30In the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite for a possession of a buryingplace.

verses.text_plain: There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife; there they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife; and there I buried Leah.
verses.verse_html: 31There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife; there they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife; and there I buried Leah.

verses.text_plain: The purchase of the field and of the cave that is therein was from the children of Heth.
verses.verse_html: 32The purchase of the field and of the cave that is therein was from the children of Heth.

verses.text_plain: And when Jacob had made an end of commanding his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, and yielded up the ghost, and was gathered unto his people.
verses.verse_html: 33And when Jacob had made an end of commanding his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, and yielded up the ghost, and was gathered unto his people.
